		<description><![CDATA[Bismillah

لاَ يضر رجُلاً لاَ يشاء عَن نفسه إلاَّ القرآن فإن كان يحب القرآن فهو يحب الله ورسوله
Abdullah Ibn Mas&#8217;ood radi Allahu anhu said: It will never harm a person that his soul does not desire more than the Qur&#8217;an, for if he loves the Qur&#8217;an; then he loves Allah and His Prophet sal Allahu alayhi [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class='snap_preview'><br /><p>Bismillah<br />
<span style="font-size:18px;line-height:normal;"><span style="color:green;"><br />
لاَ يضر رجُلاً لاَ يشاء عَن نفسه إلاَّ القرآن فإن كان يحب القرآن فهو يحب الله ورسوله</span></span><br />
Abdullah Ibn Mas&#8217;ood radi Allahu anhu said: It will never harm a person that his soul does not desire more than the Qur&#8217;an, for if he loves the Qur&#8217;an; then he loves Allah and His Prophet sal Allahu alayhi wa sallam. Kitaabu Zuhd wa Raqaaiq of Imaam Ibn Mubaarak : 1097</p>
<p>may Allah ta&#8217;ala make us from the companions of the Qur&#8217;an, Ameen.</p>
