			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class='snap_preview'><br /><p>Bismillah</p>
<p>Allah ta&#8217;ala says in surah Dhaariyaat:</p>
<p><span style="font-size:x-large;">وَالسَّمَاءِ ذَاتِ الْحُبُكِ</span></p>
<p><em>&#8220;By  the Sky, full of paths!&#8221; </em>(51:7)</p>
<p>Allah ta&#8217;ala swears an oath concerning the sky, and what it contains.</p>
<p><span style="font-size:x-large;">الْحُبُكِ</span>- is from ha-ba-kaaf (ح ب ك) and there are a few opinions on this word.</p>
<p>Firstly, it is said to be plural of <em>hibaak</em> (حباك), which is used for pathways between sand dunes or waves. They are the patterns that form on the surface of water or sand because of the wind.</p>
<p>Secondly, it is said to be plural of <em>habeekah </em>(حبيكة), which is used for a path or a route, as well as the orbit of a celestial body.</p>
<p>Allah ta&#8217;ala swears by the sky, <span style="font-size:x-large;">ذَاتِ الْحُبُكِ</span>, <em>full of paths</em>: the sky that has waves of different colors and designs, and the sky that contains pathways of the galaxies, the orbits of the heavens.</p>
<p>Have you ever witnessed the sky , <span style="font-size:x-large;">ذَاتِ الْحُبُكِ</span>?</p>
<p><span id="more-1150"></span>Here are some pictures, courtesy of <a href="http://www.boston.com/bigpicture/" target="_blank">The Big Picture</a>:</p>
<p><a href="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/a07.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1151" title="a07" src="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/a07.jpg?w=500&#038;h=284" alt="a07" width="500" height="284" /></a><a href="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/a12.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1152" title="a12" src="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/a12.jpg?w=500&#038;h=288" alt="a12" width="500" height="288" /></a><a href="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/a09.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1153" title="a09" src="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/a09.jpg?w=500&#038;h=294" alt="a09" width="500" height="294" /></a><a href="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/best-picture-gallery-northern-lights-aurora-borealis-whitehorse-yukon2-peter-lytwyniuk-pic1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1154" title="best-picture-gallery-northern-lights-aurora-borealis-whitehorse-yukon2-peter-lytwyniuk-pic1" src="http://tayyibaat.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/best-picture-gallery-northern-lights-aurora-borealis-whitehorse-yukon2-peter-lytwyniuk-pic1.jpg?w=500&#038;h=334" alt="best-picture-gallery-northern-lights-aurora-borealis-whitehorse-yukon2-peter-lytwyniuk-pic1" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p>SubhanAllah.</p>
<p>When Allah ta&#8217;ala swears an oath by something, it shows its importance and as a result, it is raised in status.</p>
