			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class='snap_preview'><br /><p>Bismillah</p>
<p>walhamdulillah,</p>
<p>Allah ta&#8217;ala says in the first ayah of  Surah Qaaf,</p>
<p><span style="font-size:large;">ق<span class="sign"> ۚ</span> وَالْقُرْآنِ الْمَجِيدِ</span></p>
<p>&#8220;Qaaf. By the Qur&#8217;an that is <em>Majeed</em>&#8221; (50:1)</p>
<p><em>Majeed </em>is from the root meem-jeem-daal (م ج د),<em> majd</em>.<em> Majeed</em> means: <em>dhul majd</em>: one that has <em>majd</em>. <em>Majd</em> is complete <em>&#8216;athamah </em>(sovereignty) and <em>sultaan </em>(authority). From the root, it is said: <em>majdatul ibl</em>, &#8220;the camel reached a vast land&#8221;. This gives us the meaning that majd is <em>wus&#8217;ah</em>, vastness and spaciousness. <em>Majeed </em>means vastness in greatness, in glory, in might, in honor and in respect.</p>
<p>How is the Qur&#8217;an <em>Majeed</em>?</p>
<p><span id="more-1118"></span></p>
<p>1- It has <em>&#8216;atheemah</em>, great status. Allah has given it the highest status of all the books sent down.</p>
<p>2- It is a <em>Muhaymin</em> over all previous books. <a href="http://tayyibaat.wordpress.com/2008/11/08/al-muhaymin-the-protector/" target="_blank"><em>Muhaymin</em></a> means one who guards and looks after. The Qur&#8217;an is authoritative and corrects the mistakes done by the people in the previous books.</p>
<p>3- It is <em>Haakim</em> (One that Judges), not <em>Mahkoom</em> (one that is judged). It is <em>Naasikh</em> (one that abrogates), not <em>Mansookh</em> (one that is abrogated). Over it nothing else can be preferred.</p>
<p>4- It has the khayr (goodness) of dunya and aakhirah.</p>
<p>The Qur&#8217;an is Majeed: exalted, very honorable, respected, perfect, complete, high status and of great might.</p>
